how to create prefit/postfit yield tables

1a (optional) : fit your usual complete datacard and stuff. Do save with uncertainties
1b : use the rebin_datacards.py script to rebin all the histograms to 1 bin. During this the bin errors will be lost -> we lose the correct AutoMCstat errors in the yield errors
     Also: ! this will change the existing template ! Te original templates will be backupped in a separate file. Check the code !

2 : create a workspace for this new datacard and 1 bin templates

3 (optional) : transfer the post-fit nuisance values of the real fit to the new 1 bin workspace like this :
               `PostFitShapes -d combined_SLDNN_DL2Dmix.txt -o test_out.root -m 125 -f fitDiagnosticscombined_SLDNN_DL2Dmix.root:fit_s --postfit --sampling --print`
                or check the docu (http://cms-analysis.github.io/CombineHarvester/post-fit-shapes.html):

4 : run FitDiagnostics on the new 1 bin workspace with a command similar to this (hint: takes ages):
    "combine -M FitDiagnostics -m 125 --rMin -5 --rMax 5 --cminDefaultMinimizerStrategy 0 --cminDefaultMinimizerTolerance 0.1 -t -1 --expectSignal 1  --saveNormalizations --saveShapes --saveOverallShapes --saveWithUncertainties --numToysForShapes 50 "

5 : edit the get_yields script to 
    a) either do only the prefit or the prefit and postfit yields (at the bottom of the script there are two functions one can use)
    b) have the proper channel names, categories etc.

6 : profit
